The paper discusses deductive synthesis and repair of functional programs, which falls under the category of programming languages (cs.PL) and software engineering (cs.SE). The use of formal methods and logical reasoning in the Leon tool suggests that it may also be relevant to the categories of logic in computer science (cs.LO) and formal languages and automata theory (cs.FL). Additionally, the use of automated synthesis techniques and the mention of reducing synthesis time suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
